<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 11 (7,200 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Keen Sight.</em></strong> The roc has advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on sight.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Multiattack.</em></strong> The roc makes two attacks: one with its beak and one with its talons.</p>

<p><strong><em>Beak.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +13 to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. Hit: 27 (4d8 + 9) piercing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Talons.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +13 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 23 (4d6 + 9) slashing damage, and the target is grappled (escape DC 19). Until this grapple ends, the target is restrained, and the roc canâ€™t use its talons on another target.</p>

